          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"getting-started-with-pyswmp\">Getting started with pyswmp</h1>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>pyswmp</strong> is a Python-wrapped Fortran library for surface wave multipathing\nray tracing on spherical and Cartesian coordinate systems\n(Hauser et al., 2008).</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">This notebook walks through the basic workflow:</span>\n<ol>\n<li>Create a velocity model</li>\n<li>Define sources and receivers</li>\n<li>Configure ray tracing options</li>\n<li>Run forward modelling</li>\n<li>Inspect and visualise results</li>\n</ol>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">All using the <strong>file-free API</strong> \u2014 no disk I/O required.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "bkHC",
      "code_hash": "47d2fb9e3bdd82ef00e9484f33bd4c37",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"1-create-a-velocity-model\">1. Create a velocity model</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><code>create_constant_velocity_model()</code> builds a 2D grid with uniform velocity.\nThe model covers a region of Australia at 0.5\u00b0 spacing with a velocity of\n3.5 km/s (typical Rayleigh wave group velocity at ~20 s period).</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "PKri",
      "code_hash": "6709cd3cc48520ee9578e7e4b4db4431",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"2-define-sources-and-receivers\">2. Define sources and receivers</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Sources and receivers are specified as <code>(longitude, latitude)</code> arrays.\n<code>source_type=1</code> indicates point sources.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "SFPL",
      "code_hash": "d58bb12d657d7dd3b6f75ff57368671e",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"3-configure-ray-tracing-options\">3. Configure ray tracing options</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><code>TrackerOptions</code> controls the numerical solver, coordinate system, and\noutput extraction. Key parameters:</span>\n<ul>\n<li><code>coordinate_system=2</code> \u2014 spherical coordinates (longitude/latitude)</li>\n<li><code>dt</code> \u2014 ODE time step size</li>\n<li><code>max_iterations</code> \u2014 maximum wavefront propagation steps</li>\n<li><code>extract_raypaths=True</code> \u2014 store individual ray paths for plotting</li>\n</ul></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "RGSE",
      "code_hash": "6a2eea9d5d580f80dc8083b19acd9a00",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"4-run-forward-modelling\">4. Run forward modelling</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Create a <code>WaveFrontTracker</code> with the model and options, then call\n<code>forward(sources, receivers)</code>. The result contains travel times, azimuths,\narrival numbers, and (optionally) ray paths.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "emfo",
      "code_hash": "59ba365136324e3aefff96bb7e6fbb55",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"5-inspect-results\">5. Inspect results</h2>\n<h3 id=\"dataframe-view\">DataFrame view</h3>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><code>to_dataframe()</code> converts results to a pandas DataFrame with columns:\n<code>source</code>, <code>receiver</code>, <code>arrival</code>, <code>time</code>, <code>azimuth</code>, <code>spreading</code>.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
